This topic describe the function of a toggle switch, usually
found on the side of a Lenovo notebook PC, which is used 
to disable the camera for privacy protection.

Some Lenovo PCs include a sliding cap on top of the built-in camera (
camera shutter) for the same purpose. There is a separate topic for
that mechanism. Check the product ID/OD and consult with your Lenovo contact
to avoid using the wrong topic.
-->
